Project3

Class Stack

  • java.lang.Object
    • Project3.Stack

  • public class Stack
extends java.lang.Object
    Create a class named Stack that will implement a stack of state objects using a singly linked list. Support the following methods.

    [Stack()]a.Constructor that creates the stack.

    [push(State)]b.A push method to push a state on the stack

    [pop()]c.A pop method to pop a state off the stack and return it.

    [printStackedList()]d.A printStack method to print the stack, see the example.

    [isEmpty()]e.An isEmpty method that returns true if the stack is empty, false otherwise

    [isFull()]f.An isFull method that always returns false

    Version:
    10/25/17
    Author:
    Ryan Geddings N01067534
